                                                                          GIT-MERGE-CONFLICT



1> Merge conflict = A merge conflict occurs when git cannot automatically merge changes
 because two branches have modified the same line of a file.


2> why does a merge conflict happen?

 = #> the same file is modified.
   # the same line is changed in different branches.
   # git cannot decide which version to keep.

3> uderstand conflict markers

 = git adds conflict markers inside the file.

 <<<<<<< HEAD
Hello Main Branch
=======
Hello Feature Login
>>>>>>> feature-login

 # meaning
  
 <<<<<<< HEAD → Current branch changes.
======= → Separator.
>>>>>>> feature-login → Incoming branch changes.

5> Resolving merge conflict .

 1. open the conflict file.
 2. decide the final code.
 3. remove all conflicts markers.
 4. save the file.

 stage the resolved file:

git add [ file name]  
git commit

